{{Quote|For the first movie, I made my own costume, I sewed it and everything. I designed it which was really cool because I've always kind of wanted to be a costume designer. And for the second movie, I designed my outfit with Trisha's help. They showed me pictures and because my character would be in a nightclub, I wanted something a bit sexy. But for this movie my costumes were probably some of the most complicated.|Katie Lucas|<ref name="ForceFamily">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iii/bts/profile/f20051221/index.html|text=The Force Runs Strong In This Family: Jett, Amanda & Katie}}</ref>}}
'''Katie Lucas''' is the adopted daughter of ''[[Star Wars]]'' creator [[George Lucas]], the younger sister of [[Amanda Lucas]], and the older sister of [[Jett Lucas]]. She appeared in several roles in the [[Prequel trilogy]], and later wrote several ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' episodes.

==Biography==
Katie Lucas had cameo appearances in all three films in the ''Star Wars'' [[prequel trilogy]]: she portrayed [[Amee]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']], though she was credited as '''Jenna Green.''' She played [[Lunae Minx/Legends|Lunae Minx]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Chi Eekway Papanoida]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']].

She also served as a writer on the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' television series.<ref name="Star Wars Insider 103">[[Star Wars Insider 103|''Star Wars Insider'' 103]]</ref> She wrote "[[Jedi Crash]]" and other episodes.<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/swtv/story/Sci_Fi_Wire_Talks_With_Katie_Lucas_120423.asp|text=''Sci Fi Wire'' Talks With Katie Lucas|date=2009-01-17|work=[[TheForce.net]]|archivedate=20190730073522}}</ref> She also introduced the 23rd episode of [[On location|''on location'']].<ref name="On location">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/onloc/23.html|series=On Location|text=Part 23 - R2-D2's Don}}</ref>

During The Main Event at [[Celebration V]], her father mentioned that she had written two episodes for [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|''The Clone Wars'']] [[The Clone Wars: Season Three|Season Three]]. One was about the family of her father's ''Revenge of the Sith'' character [[Notluwiski Papanoida/Legends|Notluwiski Papanoida]]. The other was about [[Asajj Ventress]] and her homeworld of [[Dathomir]].<ref name="SWArchive-Star Wars Celebration Main Event: Play by Play">{{SWArchive|url=fans/events/jon_stewart_george_lucas_main_event/index.html|text=''Star Wars'' Celebration Main Event: Play by Play}}</ref>

